JIT Compiler (Just-In-Time Compiler)
Part of the JVM execution engine.
Purpose: Improve performance of Java programs at runtime.
ğŸ”¹ How JVM works without JIT:
JVM uses an interpreter, which executes bytecode line by line.
This makes execution slow.
ğŸ”¹ How JIT works:
JIT compiles frequently used methods/instructions (called hotspots) into native machine code.
Instead of interpreting repeatedly, the JIT compiler stores compiled machine code.
At execution time, JVM directly executes the native machine code â†’ faster performance.
Variable in Java
A variable is a name given for a memory location.
It can hold some meaningful value within its range.
A variableâ€™s value can change during program execution.
Example:
int x = 10;
int y = 20;
x = x + y;
Memory Representation (RAM Example):
x â†’ stores value at address (e.g., 1002).

y â†’ stores value at address (e.g., 1006).
Word Breakdown:
Variable = â€œVary + ableâ€ â†’ changeable.
âœ… Key Points:

JIT Compiler = improves performance by compiling bytecode into machine code at runtime.
Variable = named memory location whose value can change during execution.
ğŸ”¹ Drawbacks of an Ordinary Variable
A variable can store only one value at a time.
int x = 12, 90; // Invalid

Stored in random memory location.
Volatile â†’ when program ends, variableâ€™s value is deleted from memory.
ğŸ‘‰ To store permanently, we use File Handling.
ğŸ”¹ What is Data Type?
Definition: Specifies the type of data a variable can store.
Describes:
Size â€” memory required in RAM.
Range â€” values it can hold. (Example: byte â†’ -128 to 127).
operations â€” allowed operations (addition, string concatenation, etc.).
ğŸ”¹ Types of Data in Java
Java has 2 main categories:

1. Primitive Data Type
Also called: primary, predefined, basic, fundamental, atomic, intrinsic.

Total: 8 types
Numeric/Integral
byte (8 bits)
short (16 bits)
int (32 bits)
long (64 bits)
Decimal
float (32 bits)
double (64 bits)
Non-Numeric
char (16 bits)
boolean (1 bit or depends on JVM)
2. Reference Data Type
Examples: class, array, interface, enum, record, etc.

âœ… Summary:

Ordinary variables â†’ store only one value, temporary.
Data type â†’ defines size, range, and operations of data.
Java has 8 primitive data types and reference data types.
ğŸ”¹ Statically Typed vs Dynamically Typed Languages
Statically Typed Language
Data type must be declared before using a variable.
Once declared, the variable holds the same type of value till program ends.
Example: C, C++, Java (JSE), C#
ğŸ‘‰ Example in Java:

int x = 10;  // must declare int
x = "Hello"; // âŒ not allowed
Dynamically Typed Language
Data type not required when declaring variables.
Variable can hold different types of values during execution.
Exaple: Python, JavaScript, Visual Basic
ğŸ‘‰ Example in Python:

x = 10
x = "Hello"  # âœ… allowed
ğŸ”¹ Comments in Java
Used to make code readable.
Ignored by the compiler.
Types of Comments:
Single-line Comment
